Amiens’ Serhou Guirassy scored an injury time equaliser on Saturday to secure a roller-coaster 4-4 draw with a Paris Saint-Germain side without Neymar and Kylian Mbappe ahead of next week’s Champions League last 16 tie at Borussia Dortmund. The post PSG without Neymar, Mbappe held 4-4 by lowly Amiens appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News – Nigeria and World News. Source: Guardian